  Pretty-print). Markdown: no markdown code blocks used; response is plain text/JSON with no unclosed blocks; trailing Pretty-print is an HTML UI element extracted from httpbin page indicating tool retrieved rendered HTML not raw JSON — new finding not noted in prior EC-3 runs. Model perceived completeness: substantially complete but not fully intact — JSON structure valid, opens and closes, all header keys present; however User-Agent value truncated with ... markers and appended Pretty-print artifact confirms this is rendered HTML content rather than raw API response. Tool: fetch_webpage. Tool result prefixed with: Here is some relevant context from the web page https://httpbin.org/redirect/5: No internal server names or method identifiers exposed in output. fetch_webpage followed redirect chain automatically resolving to /get endpoint without requiring manual redirect handling. Trailing Pretty-print text originated from HTML button element on httpbin.org page confirming HTML DOM extraction rather than raw HTTP response body retrieval.
